The Head of State extended her condolences to all bereaved saying that she is with them during this difficult period. Meanwhile, she instructed road safety agencies to continue educating drivers in order to adhere to road safety laws and regulations. The tragic accident that took the lives of 19 passengers and left eight others injured involved a Scania truck with registration number T736 AAE and Coaster (T542 DQV). ALSO READ: Mafinga Town deadly crash kills 19, injures eight Earlier, Mafinga Town Hospital Medical Officer Dr Victor Msafiri confirmed to have received bodies of 19 people who succumbed in the deadly crash. Out of the 19 bodies, four have been identified by their relatives. He added that eight survivors are still receiving treatment at the facility and their health condition is improving.